      <body>
         <head type="date">
            <date when="1805-03-30">March 30, 1805</date>
         </head>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1805-03-30.01" n="">
            <sp who="wc">
               <speaker>Clark</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>[<hi rend="italic">March 30, 1805</hi>]</date>
               </ab>
               <p>
31h of March Monday 1805    Cloudy    Several gangus of Ducks and Gees pass up    not much ice floating. All the party in high Spirits, but fiew nights pass without a Dance    they are helth. except the—vn. [venereal]—which is common with the Indians and have been communicated to many of our party at this place—    those favores bieng easy acquired. all Tranquille
</p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1805-03-30.02" n="">
            <sp who="wc">
               <speaker>Clark</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>
                     <hi rend="right">[<hi rend="italic">NB: 30th Saturday. See <name type="person" key="Ordway, John">Ordway</name> here</hi>]<ref target="n09033001" n="1"/>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">31t of March Monday 1805</hi>
                     </hi>
                  </date>
               </ab>
               <p>
Cloudy Day    Seven Gangs of Gees and Ducks pass up the river—    but a Small portion of ice floating down to day—    but fiew Inds visit us to day    all the party in high Spirits    they pass but fiew nights without amuseing themselves danceing possessing perfect harmony and good understanding towards each other    Generally healthy except venerials complains which is verry Commion amongst the natives and the men Catch it from them [<hi rend="italic">NB: Qu:</hi>]<ref target="n09033002" n="2"/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1805-03-30.03" n="">
            <sp who="ml">
               <speaker>Lewis</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>Saturday March 30th 1805<ref target="n09033003" n="3"/>
                  </date>
               </ab>
               <p>
Observed Equal Altitudes of the <seg n="u9737">☉</seg>, with Sextant and artificial Horzn. of Water.</p>
               <p>
                  <table rows="3" cols="9">
                     <row role="data">
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">A. M.</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">8</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">42</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">46</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">     </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">P. M.</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">4</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">17</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">33</cell>
                     </row>
                     <row role="data">
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"> </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">"</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">44</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">27</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"> </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"> </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">"</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">19</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">15</cell>
                     </row>
                     <row role="data">
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"> </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">"</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">46</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">10</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"> </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1"> </cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">"</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">20</cell>
                        <cell role="data" rows="1" cols="1">59</cell>
                     </row>
                  </table>
               </p>
               <p>
Altd. by Sextant at the time of observt.    49° 45' 00" 
</p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1805-03-30.04" n="">
            <sp who="jo">
               <speaker>Ordway</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date/>
               </ab>
               <p>
Saturday 30th <hi rend="italic">March 1805</hi>.    clear and pleasant    The [river] raised 10
Inches last night.    the Ice runs thick in the R. to day. The Indian Goods all put out to air. The Big Barge corked &amp; Got ready to descend the <name type="place" key="Missouri River">Missouri</name>.

</p>
            </sp>
         </div>
